The Features are made available to you free of charge for use on your mobile device. By entering into this Agreement and accessing and using the Features you represent and warrant that:
you have the legal right and ability to enter into this Agreement and to use or access the Features in accordance with the terms of this Agreement;
you are at least 14 years of age;
you are not breaching any other agreement or obligation you have with a third party or any provision of any law or regulation;
you will use the Features in accordance with the most current version of this Agreement;
all information submitted by you when using the Features shall be accurate, current and complete;
you will safeguard your information, including your Personal Code, your username and password, and will not disclose your Personal Code, user name, password or other account information related to the Features to any third party and, you will notify BIXI, as promptly as possible, if you become aware, or have any reason to suspect, that the security of your account has been compromised; and
you accept full responsibility for all activities, transactions, assessments, charges, duties, fees, and taxes and any other financial or other liability resulting from any use of the Features under your Personal Code, name or account.
Prohibitions
As a condition to your use of the Features, you agree not to:
(a) access or use any non-public areas of the Features or BIXI’s computer systems;
(b) attempt to probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of the Features or any related system or network or breach any security or authentication measures used in connection with the Features and such systems and networks;
(c) attempt to decipher, decompile, disassemble, or reverse engineer any of the software used to provide the Features;
(d) harm or threaten to harm other users in any way or interfere with, or attempt to interfere with, the access of any user, host or network, including without limitation, by sending a virus, overloading, flooding, spamming, or mail-bombing;
(e) provide any incorrect payment information or payment information belonging to a third party;
(f) use the Features in an abusive way contrary to its intended use, to its documentation or to BIXI’s reasonable instructions; or
(g) impersonate or misrepresent your affiliation with any person or entity.
BIXI will have the right to investigate and prosecute violations of any of the above, including without limitation possible infringement of any intellectual property rights and possible security breaches, to the fullest extent of the law. BIXI may involve and cooperate with law enforcement authorities in prosecuting users who violate this Agreement. You acknowledge that, although BIXI has no obligation to monitor your access to or use of the Features, it has the right to do so for the purpose of operating the Features, to ensure your compliance with this Agreement, or to comply with applicable law or the order or requirement of a court, administrative agency, or other governmental body.
Proprietary Rights
All right, title, and interest in and to the Features are and will remain the exclusive property of BIXI and its licensors. The Features are protected by copyright, trademark, and other domestic and foreign laws concerning intellectual property. Except as expressly permitted in this Agreement, you may not reproduce, modify, or create derivative works based upon, distribute, sell, transfer, publicly display, publicly perform, transmit, or otherwise use the Features.
Privacy
What personal information do we have access to when you use the Features?
When you use the Features, we collect or have access to the following personal information:
Personal information in your account such as your name, physical address, mailing address and telephone number;
Geolocation data. For example, once you consent to it, we access your mobile device’s geolocation data to give you information about the stations that are closest to you;
Data about how you use BIXI bicycles, such as geolocation data, routes taken and the rental status of bicycles;
Personal information related to your mobile device, such as your IP address;
Billing data.
When you purchase a subscription through the App, our online payment providers collect certain personal information such as payment data (for example, the number, CVV code and expiration date of the payment card). BIXI does not have access to this information, which is encrypted and used by the online payment providers in compliance with PCI-DSS standards. Information thus collected is kept on servers that may be located outside Canada, particularly in the United States.
How is your information collected or accessed by BIXI?
Insofar as possible, we obtain personal information directly you, with your consent. However, we may gather or access personal information from third parties when you consent to such collection or if permitted by law.
We collect and gain access to your personal information through various means, particularly when:
You log in to your account on our App;
You consent to sharing your mobile device’s geolocation data;
You use BIXI bicycles;
You contact us.
You may choose not to provide some personal information, but you will then not be able to take advantage of certain Features of our App.
What do we use your personal information for?
We mainly use your personal information:
To provide the Features, including to locate BIXI bicycles and stations used in the System;
To communicate with you about your account and to provide customer service in a timely manner when necessary;
To improve the quality of the Features;
To verify proper use of the Features;
For any other purpose permitted by law that we may identify from time to time.
Who do we share your personal information with?
Only BIXI staff members whose duties so require, its partners and service providers (for example, providers of hosting and online payment services) will have access to the personal information gathered hereunder, to the extent that such access is required for the purposes set out in this Agreement. BIXI may also make this personal information accessible to third parties to comply with a law or court order.
Is your personal information sent outside of Québec?
Personal information collected or accessed by BIXI is hosted on secure servers which may be located outside of Québec, particularly in Canada and the United States. In this case, BIXI requires commitments regarding protection of personal information from its service providers.
How long do we keep your personal information?
BIXI keeps your personal information only for the time necessary for the purposes provided in this Agreement and to comply with legal and regulatory obligations. After this time, your personal information will be destroyed or anonymized.
How do we protect the privacy of your personal information?
The personal information we collect or have access to is kept confidential in accordance with the laws applicable to the protection of personal information. Furthermore, reasonable administrative, technical and physical measures will be taken to protect the Personal Information from loss, theft, or unauthorized access or use.
What are your rights?
Under the law, you have certain rights, such as the following:
The right to have the confidentiality of your personal information protected;
The right to access and correct your personal information;
Where applicable, the right to withdraw your consent to the disclosure or use of your personal information.
At any time, you may also remove your email from our newsletter mailing list by clicking on the unsubscribe link that appears at the bottom of the newsletter or by contacting us (see the “
Contact
” section below).
